\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 Contour\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A unified LFO / point-reduce / transform toolkit for REAPER track envelopes, automation items, and MIDI CC \u8212- all in one ReaImGui panel.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Generate} \u8212- draw LFO shapes (sine, square, saw, triangle, parametric, ...) onto the target, with a live, non-destructive preview that matches REAPER's native CC LFO.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Reduce} \u8212- thin point density with an adjustable tolerance (live, non-destructive).\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Transform} \u8212- a mouse overlay to stretch / scale / compress / warp / tilt / reverse / flip the selected points or time selection directly under the cursor.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Dependencies (install separately via ReaPack \u8212- NOT bundled)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b ReaImGui} \u8212- the panel UI\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b js_ReaScriptAPI} \u8212- the Transform overlay\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b SWS extension} \u8212- the Transform overlay\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Actions installed\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Contour} \u8212- the main panel\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Contour Transform} \u8212- the mouse-overlay tool (also runnable on its own / hotkey-bindable)\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Licensed under the GNU GPL v3 (or later). See the LICENSE file in the repository.\par}
}
